Checklist mapping for the current web app

Inputs used by implemented checks:
- TOC XML / e-rights XML
- Paper PDF extracted from the uploaded ZIP
- HotCRP ACM settings HTML
- ACM e-Right HTML
- Track review state saved locally by the app

Displayed checklist items

1. PDF title matches metadata
   Status: automated.
   Sources: PDF + XML.
   Maps to original item 1: title consistency across submitted paper, HotCRP/XML metadata, and e-right metadata.
   Current behavior: checks whether the XML title appears in extracted PDF text.

2. PDF author list matches metadata
   Status: automated.
   Sources: PDF + XML.
   Maps to original item 1: author-list consistency.
   Current behavior: checks whether each XML author name appears in extracted PDF text.

3. PDF affiliations match metadata
   Status: automated.
   Sources: PDF + XML.
   Maps to original item 1: affiliation consistency.
   Current behavior: checks whether XML affiliations appear in extracted PDF text when affiliation text is available.

4. All author emails in metadata appear in the PDF
   Status: automated.
   Sources: PDF + XML.
   Maps to original items 1 and 8: email consistency and all author emails present in the camera-ready PDF.
   Current behavior: checks whether each XML author email appears in extracted PDF text.

5. All authors have ORCID in metadata
   Status: automated.
   Sources: XML.
   Maps to original item 6: every author provides ORCID.
   Current behavior: checks whether every XML author record has an ORCID value.

6. ACM keywords added on HotCRP
   Status: automated.
   Sources: HotCRP ACM HTML.
   Maps to original item 2: include ACM keywords.
   Current behavior: checks HotCRP ACM proceeding messages for missing ACM keyword warnings.

7. ACM Computing Classification added on HotCRP
   Status: automated.
   Sources: HotCRP ACM HTML.
   Maps to original item 3: include ACM Computing Classification / CCS.
   Current behavior: checks HotCRP ACM proceeding messages for missing CCS warnings.

8. References added on HotCRP
   Status: automated.
   Sources: HotCRP ACM HTML.
   Maps to original item 4: include references.
   Current behavior: checks HotCRP ACM proceeding messages for missing reference warnings.

9. Source files submitted
   Status: automated.
   Sources: HotCRP ACM HTML.
   Maps to original item 5: submit source files for the camera-ready version.
   Current behavior: checks whether the HotCRP ACM row includes source-file archive links.

10. Other issues
    Status: automated.
    Sources: HotCRP ACM HTML.
    Maps to original item 10: fix HotCRP format-check warnings and errors.
    Current behavior: reports per-paper HotCRP ACM proceeding warnings and errors, including missing fonts, bad fonts, missing ACM metadata, missing references, and other messages shown in the HTML.

11. PDF DOI matches e-Right
    Status: automated.
    Sources: PDF + e-Right.
    Maps to original item 1: copyright/license metadata consistency across submitted paper and e-right form.
    Current behavior: checks whether the DOI from the matching e-Right row appears in extracted PDF text.

12. PDF ISBN matches e-Right
    Status: automated.
    Sources: PDF + e-Right.
    Maps to original item 1: copyright/license metadata consistency across submitted paper and e-right form.
    Current behavior: checks whether the ISBN from the matching e-Right rights details appears in extracted PDF text.

13. PDF copyright type matches e-Right
    Status: automated.
    Sources: PDF + e-Right.
    Maps to original item 1: copyright/license metadata consistency across submitted paper and e-right form.
    Current behavior: checks whether the copyright type from the matching e-Right rights details appears in extracted PDF text.

14. Paper PDF provided
    Status: automated.
    Sources: ZIP.
    App-specific intake check.
    Current behavior: confirms the uploaded ZIP contains a matching local paper PDF.

15. PDF has no visible page numbers
    Status: automated heuristic.
    Sources: PDF.
    Maps to proceedings formatting requirements.
    Current behavior: scans extracted PDF text near page boundaries for standalone page-number-like text.

16. Latest ACM template used
    Status: chair review.
    Sources: PDF + HotCRP.
    Maps to original item 7: use the latest ACM template.
    Current behavior: defaults to manual review, with HotCRP class/status shown in the note.

17. Authors stacked individually
    Status: chair review.
    Sources: PDF.
    Maps to original item 9: authors should be stacked individually according to ACM interim layout guidance.
    Current behavior: defaults to manual review.

18. Last page balanced
    Status: chair review.
    Sources: PDF.
    Maps to original item 11: last page should be balanced.
    Current behavior: defaults to manual review.

19. Track-specific page limit followed
    Status: chair review.
    Sources: HotCRP ACM HTML + rules.
    Maps to original item 12: follow the track-specific page limit.
    Current behavior: defaults to manual review until authoritative track/page-limit rules are configured.

Follow-up review support

- A follow-up review can be created from any review with issue papers.
- Follow-up checks inherit checklist items and issue papers from the parent review.
- A parent review is locked after a follow-up is created.
- Follow-up results tag issues as new, still present, or fixed by comparing with the parent review.
